shared_text:
Mammoth Middle School
July 31, 2018 at 3:10 PM ·

The beginning of the school year is right around the corner, and I hope you all had a lovely summer! I know the fires have been a worry. We are keeping all the firefighters and victims' families of the fires in our hearts. Hopefully, it will be contained soon, and no more lives will be lost.

I just wanted to remind everyone that registration begins August 13th in the main office of the middle school. Please come in to pick up your registration packet and turn it in once it is completed. Students will then be able to receive their class schedules. If you have any questions or concerns about the schedule, we will be able to address it when school begins. We allow a two week grace period as the high school does to make any corrections. Our wonderful school counselor, Kelley Jayne, will be able to assist the students.

See you soon!
Dr. Rinaldi

The free public screening will be held in the Multipurpose Room at Mammoth High School on Tuesday, May 1st at 5PM. Student projects on the topic of Social Justice will be on display at the screening. For more information, please contact Laura Timpano at ltimpano@monocoe.org or 760-934-0031.

shared_text:
Mike Vowels-Skier
March 23, 2018 at 12:57 PM ·

Things are about to get very busy. My ski film shows in Truckee, CA on April 11; one day before the start of the Snowsports History Celebration, in Squaw Valley. On April 13, we drive to Mammoth Mountain for a ski day, and my film shows that night in the town of Mammoth Lakes.

Early Saturday morning we drive back to Squaw Valley for a ski day, and that night we attend the Ski & Snowboard Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony Dinner Event.

Threaded into all of this, Cate and I are being hosted for a ski day by: Heavenly, Northstar, Kirkwood, Sierra at Tahoe, Homewood, and IMPORTANTLY, our Host Tahoe Donner, who I have partnered with for our film showing at the Alder Creek Adventure Center.

Please share this Post with your FB Friends who live in either the Lake Tahoe area or the Mammoth Mountain Community.

post_text: Calling all babysitters!
shared_text:
Mammoth Hospital
October 24, 2017 at 4:45 PM ·

Do you know any kids ages 11-13 who want to learn more about babysitting? Mammoth Hospital is offering Safe Sitter babysitting preparation courses designed to prepare students in grades 6-8 to be safe when they're home alone, watching younger siblings or babysitting. Students learn to care for a choking infant or child, injury prevention and management, safety for the sitter, child care essentials, behavior management, and learn about babysitting as a business.

For more info on this great training opportunity coming up Sunday, November 12th, contact Kathy Romagnino at (760) 924-4063.

post_text: Great Job MHS athletes!!
shared_text:
Mammoth High School Athletics
September 24, 2017 at 8:52 AM ·

WEEKEND RECAP:

Husky Cross Country was DYNAMIC in the Mammoth Invitational. Our girl's team won with 6 top ten finishes and first place overall. Boy's team had 3 top ten finishes and second place overall. Important to note, that second place finish for boys is a mere 3 POINTS out of 1st place, held by CA State Champions Desert Christian. 3 points behind the state champs. Way to go, runners! ❤️🏃‍♀️🏃🏽💛

MHS Volleyball swept through Boron at home, both JV and Varsity won their matches in 3 sets in our first league games. ❤️🏐💛

Husky Football traveled to Fresno Christian on Friday. We lost the game but had a good trip and represented our school in a way we can be proud of. Our first league football game is this Friday in Lone Pine. ❤️🏈💛

MHS Volleyball swept through Boron at home, both JV and Varsity won their matches in 3 sets in our first league games. ❤️🏐💛
